        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Appleton will bring out the new Edit of the Descent in the U. States, so that your work will now tell in 3 Edits.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>C. D. <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">Dec. 2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>.</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_135.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">D. Appleton &amp; Co</ref>, CD’s US publisher, had agreed to publish the second edition of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> in the US (letter from <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_135.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">D. Appleton &amp; Co</ref>., [<hi rend="italic">c.</hi> 19] November 1874). George had helped edit this edition (<ref target="./DCP-LETT-9735.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to G. H. Darwin, 27 November [1874]</ref>). A German translation was also being prepared (<ref target="./DCP-LETT-9700.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from J. V. Carus, 27 October 1874</ref>).</note>
        </div>        
            
